text:
No. 48 Womenâ€™s Tennis Dominates in 7-0 Win Over Shippensburg
No. 48 Goldey-Beacom did not drop a set in its first match of the season as a nationally ranked team, rolling to a 7-0 triumph over Shippensburg at Delcastle Tennis Center in Wilmington, DE. Juniors Nahomi Quinonez (Manta, Ecuador) and Jess Sanzo (Bristol, England) got things going with a 6-0 victory over Ava Kalist and Kendall Winters at third doubles. Seniors Elizabeth Mova (Sevastopol, Ukraine) and Macy Hendin-Walker (Ipswich, England) clinched the doubles point with a 6-1 triumph at No. 2 doubles over Corinne Markovich and Jade Miller.
